race.description: Pearce Racing Yearling Parade Tomorrow Handicap
race.comment: FANCY RED (1) held on to score narrowly over 1400m and now she can really spread her wings getting out to the mile. The wide draw is a niggle, though Nottle's claim is a bonus and she looks ready to go to the next level. Been a slow build this time in work but she can explode now. STREET BAND (9) just missed two back before coming out to the mile last time out and finishing 1.4L off the winner. O'Donnell remains in the saddle and he's inching closer to a drought-breaking win. Can lob in a good position and be in this for a very long way. ASIF (7) steps out to the mile again today after showing good improvement last start behind FANCY RED. He's a winner at the mile previously and the winkers go on for the first time. Watch for him late in the race. DEAMBER (8) is better than she showed last time out and can bounce back with the senior jockey back on board. GREAT FORTUNE (4) wasn't far away last time out and can be in the finish.
